To solve this, we first find the slope of the line between the first two points $(2,2)$ and $(9,11)$:
\begin{align*}
\text{Slope} &= \frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1} \\
&= \frac{11 - 2}{9 - 2} \\
&= \frac{9}{7}
\end{align*}
Next, we use this slope to determine which point does not ensure a line with those two points. The points on the line based on the slope will satisfy:
\begin{align*}
y - y_1 &= m(x - x_1) \\
y - 2 &= \frac{9}{7}(x - 2)
\end{align*}
Substituting the remaining points into this equation will reveal which point is not on the line.

